news.title: Rajasthan housing board earns Rs 21 crore by selling 205 flats in a day
news.para: RHB commissioner Pawan Arora said, "The RHB schemes are receiving good response from residents as it caters to all sections of society. The e-auction is organised every Wednesday."

news.title: Telangana government to check building nod in 74 new municipalities
news.para: The municipal commissioners have been asked to check permissions of major constructions, especially apartments and gated communities, that were granted by erstwhile gram panchayats which are now part of new municipalities.

news.title: Two lakh houses ready, wait for buyers in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: In Indore there are around 62,000 units while in Bhopal 33,000 units and in Jabalpur 20,000 units are remaining to be sold in all categories, as per the real estate regulatory authority.

news.title: Bajaj Electricals board approves review of corporate structure
news.para: ​The company said it would explore a full range of options and alternatives, including demerger, subsidiarisation and strategic partnerships.

news.title: Housing prices may rise 5% during 2022: Report
news.para: On the housing segment, the report said that sales momentum is expected to continue in 2022 as prospective homebuyers' preferences for bigger homes, better amenities, and attractive pricing will keep them interested to seal the deals.

news.title: China Evergrande defaults on its debt. Now what?
news.para: Fitch Ratings had placed the Chinese property developer in its “restricted default” category. But instead of resolving questions about the fate of the Chinese behemoth, the announcement only deepened them.

news.title: Plots near Noida airport at cheap rates? YEIDA warns buyers, goes to cops
news.para: Officials said most of the advertisements that offered YEIDA-notified land at runaway rates were posted on social media and were attracting buyers from far and wide. On Thursday, YEIDA submitted screenshots of these ads to the police and asked buyers not to fall for such tall claims.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Now, realtors will have to give 5% land to government in new layouts
news.para: The government's decision has alarmed the realty sector and property buyers. The realtors fear that the decision would eat into their margins which have already become thin due to Covid-19 and would make their business unviable.

news.title: Jaypee Wish Town residents protest upkeep fees hike
news.para: The residents demanded immediate rollback of the increased upkeep fees levied from December 2021 as well as additional charges levied on the services of electrician, plumber and sweeper during each visit.

news.title: Shriram Properties initial share sale gets subscribed 1.63 times on second day
news.para: For 2,93,51,639 shares on sale, bids to the tune of 4,77,23,750 were received on the second day. This translates to the offer getting subscribed 1.63 times, according to data available with the BSE.

news.title: Fitch downgrades Evergrande & Kaisa after missed payment deadlines
news.para: The downgrades to so-called "restricted default" status come even though Evergrande and Kaisa have not officially announced defaults that could result in drawn-out debt restructuring processes.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group kicks off $12 billion debt restructuring: Source
news.para: Kaisa, China's largest holder of offshore debt among developers after China Evergrande Group, did not repay $400 million of bonds that matured on Tuesday, triggering cross-default provision on all its offshore bonds and prompting a downgrade to "restricted default" by Fitch Ratings.

news.title: Mumbai: HC frowns at Mhada lottery clause for Swan Mills workers
news.para: “Prima facie this does not appeal to us and needs to be rectified,” said Justices Gautam Patel and Madhav Jamdar on a petition by Girni Kamgar Sabha and nearly 50 allottees against Mhada’s June 20, 2012, circular that split Swan Mills into two codes for allotments.

news.title: Mohali civic body to use tiles, paver blocks made of construction waste
news.para: The plant has been made functional and was inspected by Mohali Mayor Amarjit Singh Sidhu alias Jeeti Sidhu on Wednesday. Sidhu said the MC has taken up various initiatives to bring Mohali at number one in the sanitation survey.

news.title: Parliamentary panel seeks details on status of Delhi master plan-2021
news.para: The committee, in its original report on the subject, had desired that the "high-level committee" of the DDA meet at periodic intervals for reviewing, monitoring and managing the master plan, so as to enable achieving the targets, the parliamentary panel said.
